        <title>Posted Wild L.A.: Mountain Lions, Grizzly Bears &amp; the Land that Once Was to SoCal Focus</title>
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.kcet.org/updaily/socal_focus/history/la-as-subject/wild-la-mountain-lions-grizzly-bears-and-the-land.html" />
        <id>tag:www.kcet.org,2011:/updaily/socal_focus//1239.38311</id>
        <published>2011-09-15T22:30:00Z</published>
        <updated>2011-09-16T21:29:05Z</updated>
        <summary>A series of recent news headlines have reminded us that our city--often associated with brown skies, high-speed pavement, and its concrete river--still maintains an intimate relationship with nature. 
</summary>
        <author>
            <name>Nathan Masters</name>
            <uri>http://www.kcet.org/cgi-bin/mt/mt-cp.cgi?__mode=view&amp;blog_id=1239&amp;id=2075</uri>
        </author>
        <category term="Environment" scheme="http://www.sixapart.com/ns/types#category" /><category term="LA as Subject" scheme="http://www.sixapart.com/ns/types#category" />
