        <title>Posted Photos: How Oil Wells Once Dominated Southern California&apos;s Landscape to SoCal Focus</title>
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.kcet.org/updaily/socal_focus/history/la-as-subject/photos-oil-extraction-in-socal-history-35788.html" />
        <id>tag:www.kcet.org,2011:/updaily/socal_focus//1239.35788</id>
        <published>2011-08-11T22:00:00Z</published>
        <updated>2011-08-11T05:29:39Z</updated>
        <summary>Ever since oil was discovered near downtown L.A. in 1892, extracting petroleum from the land beneath has been a major part of the Southern California economy.</summary>
        <author>
            <name>Nathan Masters</name>
            <uri>http://www.kcet.org/cgi-bin/mt/mt-cp.cgi?__mode=view&amp;blog_id=1239&amp;id=2075</uri>
        </author>
        <category term="LA as Subject" scheme="http://www.sixapart.com/ns/types#category" />
